  "text": "To estimate carbon respiration by mussels, we multiplied the areal mussel O 2 consumption rates by a molar respiratory quotient of 1 : 1.1 (O 2 /C; [CITATION_1] . Respired carbon fluxes from mussels were 300 6 100; 2000 6 700; and 1200 6 400 mg C m 22 d 21 on 21 August, 1 September, and 10 September, respectively. Daily respired carbon fluxes from mussels were estimated by linear interpolation and summed to give a total flux of 27,000 6 9000 mg C m 22 , or 1300 6 400 mg C m 22 d 21 (Fig. 4e, gray fill) . By comparison, summed POC fluxes from the water column were 23,000 6 2000 mg C m 22 , or 1100 6 100 mg C m 22 d 21 (Fig. 4e, black  fill) .",
